MBOMBELA – A taxi that was allegedly transporting pupils to a camp was involved in an accident with a Range Rover on the N4 tonight. According to Hi-Tech Medical Services paramedic Anilda Groenewald, all the patients were either transported to Mediclinic Nelspruit or Rob Ferreira Hospital. “The patients had minor to moderate injuries.” In another accident that happened near Vivo filling station at Schoemanskloof, a taxi collided with a cow on the road.  Emer-G-Med operations manager Martin Jeffrey said all the passengers and the driver were not injured. “The cow did die at the scene.” 